        <div id='cisminer-content' class="col-sm-9 col-md-9">
          <h1 class="page-header">Welcome to the regulatory modules search web!</h1>
          <p class="lead">
            <strong>CisMiner</strong> is an online tool to search for putative Cis-Regulatory Modules genome-wide. Our computational methodology screens the provided genome or regions for Transcription Factor Binding Sites and searches for clusters using fuzzy technology. Fuzzy clustering overcomes the problem of sharp boundaries, where relevant Transcription Factor Binding Sites for the discovered Cis-Regulatory Modules could be arbitrarily omitted or viceversa due to an arbitrary sharp distance threshold otherwise. In addition, cutting-edge Transcription Factor databases and scan tools are used for our search. 
          </p>
          <p class="lead">
            If you want to perform an <strong>Analysis</strong>, fill out the form on the left. If you just want to give it a try, click on the <strong>Demo</strong> button. If you want to know more about regulatory modules, go to the <strong><a href="./about">About</a></strong> section or go to the <a href="./help"><strong>help section</strong></a>. 
          </p>
          <p class="lead">
            Regulatory modules is a tool developed in the <strong>Department of Computer Science and Artificial Intelligence</strong> at the <strong>University of Granada</strong>.
          </p>
      </div>



